@node "Options" "Options"
                                                                      
@{"DzA    " link "read" 0}
@{"Mail   " link "dcg" 0}
@{"HistorY" link "history" 0} 
@{"Help   " link "help" 0}

@{b}Pack@{ub} using the Pack Button...
Choose Options : LhA, LzX or DmS
You can pack any file or files also any directory or directories or both...
If NO filename is choosen a requester will popup and ask you to Go_Again.
DmS will only pack Volumes.

@{b}UnPack@{ub} using the UnPack Button... 
Automactically recogniszes packed files : (LhA|LzH|LzX|DmS|ZiP)
UnPack to any destination.
Don't try to UnPack DmS to Ram :(

@{b}Quit@{ub} Thanks an So Long...


@{b}DzA@{ub} will also inform you of the time taken to Pack or UnPack a File...

                                @{"BACK" link "main" 0

@endnode

@node "History" "History"

 History:2.0
=============
Added function to convert betwwen LhA and LzX. 
((Uses (Ram:) as Temp directory...You may need extra memory  :( ))

 History:2.0a
==============
Few internal problems solved..
Cleaned up requesters..
Added Counter to Pack/Unpack..

 History:2.1
=============
New Look GUI...
Solved problem with (Ram Disk:)...
Recongnizes Packed files automatically to be UnPacked...
Added UnZip support for zip files (UnZip must be in C:...).

 History:2.1a
==============
Added function to continue or start from new.
Automactically remembers last postion to continue.

 History:2.2
==============
You can now select your own path for Temp directory.
Will create a Directory called lha or lzx depending on file to be converted.
Will be deleted when conversion is complete.

 History:2.2a
==============
Bug fix on DMS function recongnizes Ram Disk:...
(Will not pack or unpack to Ram Disk:)...
Removed Convert... =(

 History:3.0
==============
This version will pack zip files...
But will not pack zip files using multiselect...
You will have to pack one at a time...
Sorry!!!

 History:3.1
==============
Opens window for information and progress...
A few problems in arexx script solved...


                                   @{"BACK" link "main" 0

@endnode


